THE VIDEO WAS CALLED THE TEMPLE OF KNOWLEDGE.
BACK IN THE 1940S AND 50S THE CUSTODIANS OF THE LIBRARIES USED TO HAVE LIVING QUARTERS IN THE LIBRARY.
CLARK WAS ONE OF THE CUSTODIANS
HE LIVED WITH HIS WIFE AND SON IN THE LIBRARY.
HIS SON ROBERT THOUGHT THEY WERE RICH AND HIS FATHER ALMOST CHOKED ON HIS DINNER.
HE TOLD HIS SON THAT THEY WERE POOR.
MR CLARK WORKED VERY HARD CLEANING UP WRAPPERS.
HE WAXED EVERYTHING INCLUDING THE TOPS OF THE BOOK SHELVES.
WHEN ROBERT STOOD ON THE STAIRS AND LOOKED DOWN AT THE BOOK SHELVES THEY GLEAMED.
ROBERT WAS ASHAMED OF WHERE HE LIVED AND NEVER INVITED ANYONE OVER.
THE KIDS AT SCHOOL MADE FUN OF HIM FOR LITERALLY LIVING IN THE LIBRARY.
ROBERT WOULD READ A LOT AND SOMETIMES HE WOULD GO DOWN TO THE LIBRARY AND READ IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT.
HE COULD ALWAYS FIND THE ANSWERS TO HIS QUESTIONS BECAUSE HE HAD ACCESS TO ALL THE BOOKS.
ROBERT WORKED HARD AND WENT TO COLLEGE AND EVENTUALLY BECAME A COLLEGE PROFESSOR.
HE WAS VERY PROUD OF THE DAY HE COULD TAKE HIS FATHER TO HIS OFFICE AND SHOW HIM PROFESSOR CLARK ON THE DOOR.
IT MADE HIS FATHER HAPPY AND PROUD.
ROBERT KNEW THAT IT WAS BECAUSE OF LIVING IN THE LIBRARY.
BACK IN THE 40S AND 50S CUSTODIANS OF THE LIBRARY LIVED IN THE LIBRARY
MR CLARK WAS ONE OF THESE MEN
HE LIVED AT THE LIBRARY WITH HIS SON AND DAUGHTER AND WIFE.
ROBERT, HIS SON THOUGHT THEY WERE RICH
HE ANNOUNCED THIS AT DINNER AND HIS FATHER CHOKED ON HIS FOOD.
HIS FATHER EXPLAINED THAT THEY WERE ACTUALLY POOR.
ROBERT DID LOVE TO READ, BUT HE WAS ASHAMED OF LIVING IN THE LIBRARY.
HE NEVER INVITED ANYONE OVER AND KIDS MADE FUN OF HIM FOR LIVING IN THE LIBRARY.
HIS FATHER CALLED THE LIBRARY THE TEMPLE OF KNOWLEDGE.
ROBERT LOVED TO READ AND WOULD OFTEN GO INTO THE LIBRARY IN THE NIGHT TO READ OR FIND ANSWERS TO HIS QUESTIONS.
SOMETIMES HE WOULD STAY IN THE LIBRARY UNTIL 2 OR 3 IN THE MORNING.
ROBERT LOVED BOOKS SO MUCH THAT HE WORKED HARD AND WENT TO COLLEGE EVEN THOUGH NO ONE ELSE IN HIS FAMILY HAD EVEN FINISHED HIGH SCHOOL.
HE TOOK HIS FATHER TO SEE HIS OFFICE WITH PROFESSOR CLARK ON THE DOOR.
HIS FATHER GOT VERY QUIET BUT HE WAS PROUD.
ROBERTS FATHER WORKED HARD IN THE LIBRARY AND WAXED EVERYTHING-EVEN THE TOPS OF THE BOOK CASES.
ROBERT LOVED THAT HE GOT TO LIVE IN A LIBRARY.
